The article discusses how business investment has played a significant role in rescuing the U.S. economy and accelerating its growth. It attributes this success to tax reform and deregulation, which have reduced political uncertainty and encouraged companies to invest and repatriate profits. The fourth-quarter growth in 2018 was higher than expected, with business investment making a significant contribution. The article suggests that when politicians get out of the way, the American economy becomes a strong engine of prosperity.